    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Smythe</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 39.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am in receipt of your No. 51, of the 8th
                            instant, reporting the sale of the steam yacht <hi rend="italic">Natalie</hi>, and requesting instructions in connection
                            therewith.</p>
                <pb facs="0392" n="342" xml:id="pg_342"/>
                <p>The bill of sale having been sent to the Treasury, no instructions in
                            respect to the transaction seem at present necessary.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
